1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Al Petrie for his service to the Lakeview Civic Improvement Association.
3 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Al Petrie for his incredible civic-
4 mindedness and to commend him for his service to the Lakeview Civic Improvement
5 Association; and
6 WHEREAS, Mr. Petrie is a past president of the Lakeview Civic Improvement
7 Association and the president and co-founder of Friends of Lakeview; in these roles, he has
8 united citizens with the aim of strengthening the Lakeview neighborhood in New Orleans,
9 Louisiana; and
10 WHEREAS, following Hurricane Katrina, Mr. Petrie led efforts to restore
11 Lakeview's green spaces to areas where families can gather, children can play, and neighbors
12 can reconnect with one another; and
13 WHEREAS, Mr. Petrie provided a vision for rebuilding and dedicated his energy to
14 rejuvenating Lakeview; he is a cofounder of the New Basin Canal Park restoration and
15 beautification project, which involved the installation of sidewalks, lanterns, and trees; and
16 WHEREAS, Mr. Petrie continues to serve Lakeview and demonstrates community
17 pride and resilience for the area's residents; he is truly most deserving of the highest
18 recognition for his outstanding efforts.
19 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
20 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Al Petrie for his service to the Lakeview
